HEADWORD: Contradance
<hw>Con"tra*dance`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>contra-</ets> + <ets>dance</ets>: cf. F. <ets>contrdance</ets>. Cf.
<er>Country-dance</er>.]</ety> <def>A dance in which the partners are
arranged face to face, or in opposite lines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

